errors.solution: (E.4) Their account probably has verify_strict: [ delivery ] on, it needs to be verify: [delivery]. Make a dev request to have it changed if customer wants.

(E.5) This means that the Client ID and/or Client Secret for DHL is invalid, and you'll need to receive new creds in order for this to work. Or they are using Test creds on a Prod account, or reversed.

questions.question: What are the accepted label sizes and formats?
I am unable to pull a DHL manifest, it never loads
questions.answer: (Q.2) They are probably trying to create a manifest from the parent account, which isn't supported. You need to actually login as a user on the child account to create a DHL manifest.

questions.question: The shipping labels arent printing the address line 2.
questions.answer: (Q.8) When the address2 field doesn't show up on the generated label, it's due to how EasyPost's Address Validation system formats the address2 field. Investigate and validate the address.

questions.question: We are requesting settings for DDP and DAP on international shipments.
questions.answer: (Q.9) You can specify incoterms using the incoterms field within the request body of a POST /shipments/ship request. This is located within the parcels[i].service_options.incoterms.

questions.question: When using the rates API call there is a section in the request where you can specify which “services” you want to use?
questions.answer: (Q.10) The include_services field in the request body of a rate request is an array, and the elements nested within this array should be strings or integers representing the Service IDs you wish to filter for and are comma delimited.

questions.question: Is third party billing of duty/tax ready and configurable today in eHub?
questions.answer: (Q.16) To be able to include information about 3rd party and alternate billing, you will do so using the alternate_billing object within the request body of a shipment creation request (POST /shipments/ship). The alternate_billing object should be nested under shipment.parcels[i].service_options.alternate_billing.alternate_billing.

questions.question: I was printing some labels with our test account today and then attempting to cancel them, but I keep on getting a message saying the shipment has already been shipped.
questions.answer: (Q.17) When using a Test USPS account, which is currently enabled on your eHub test account, you have a 1-2 minute window to cancel the shipment before cancellation requests are rejected. If you miss this window, it's of no consequence, as charges do not apply to these test USPS labels, which are generated as voided.

questions.question: How do I send the hazmat announcement in the API?
questions.answer: ( Q.18)To create a label for a package that contains hazmat materials, you'll need to include a specific parameter within your shipment creation request. This parameter is 'dangerous_goods.details.type' and should be nested in the following location: `shipment.parcels[i].service_options.dangerous_goods.details.type`. You will want to put the hazmat code you'll want to pass as the value of the 'type' key.

questions.question: This is a one rate shipment. Our customer is questioning that the rate should be $18 but it was returned as $20. Why was One Rate not triggered?
questions.answer: (Q.21) From EasyPost - FedEx has a live rating API, which means we don't control any of the rates that are returned in any way. We just pass the data you've supplied to FedEx and then return whatever information they send to us

questions.question: I was able to get a label using service_id 408 whereas they are requesting service_id 403. I’m not getting 403 back in a rate request?
questions.answer: (Q.22) 403 and 408 are both FedEx SmartPost. 403 is a holdover from several years ago so it won't work, 408 has to be used. The only difference is that 403 is listed under `external_carrier_name` `FedEx`, while 408 is under `FedExSmartPost`.

questions.question: Why are some of my rate requests coming back with 0 or null delivery days?
questions.answer: (Q.24) Ultimately, we don't have much control over if the delivery days are returned to us or not, as these come from EasyPost and they retrieve them directly from the carrier's API.

questions.question: Why am I not receiving any notifications from the WebHook?
questions.answer: (Q.26) We tried 5 times to send an update and it was not received. Therefore, it was turned off. To see if a webhook is disabled, make a GET /subscriptions request.

questions.question: I am sending a package to this PO BOX address but the zip code keeps changing from 29414 to 29402.
questions.answer: (Q.27) All PO box addresses have a distinct zip code depending on which office the PO box is physically located.  PO Boxes will not have the same zip code as the Post Office street address.

questions.question: Can I register multiple accounts for the same carrier? i.e. 3 different UPS accounts?
questions.answer: (Q.29) You cannot have multiple carrier accounts linked to a single customer account. To use multiple carrier accounts, you'll need to create sub-accounts, each with its own user and API token.

questions.question: When we created a test order, Media Mail was not an option. Is there something special we need to do for it to trigger?
questions.answer: (Q.30) The reason Media Mail isn't appearing in your rate requests is that it doesn't automatically display, even if you have it enabled. To access Media Mail, you need to have a rate shop rule enabled. This is necessary because Media Mail is specifically for items like books, DVDs, CDs, etc., and you need to be able to specify if the order is one of those items.

questions.question: I don't want to use /shipments/ship. Is there any other way to create a label?
questions.answer: (Q.31) You can create a shipment (POST api/v2/shipments), get the shipment ID and store it, then run a ship call on that ID (PUT api/v2/shipments/{ID}/ship).

questions.question: Is USPS Ground Advantage a service that is automatically included in a USPS account? Or does it specifically need to be activated or plugged in?
questions.answer: (Q.33) It's included in the list of available services that get added when you use a test API. But it's not added by default for Prod, it needs to be requested.
